oc:kn_198cfe60 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any Quarkus Java class to Kotlin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Detect Quarkus imports (io.quarkus.*, javax.enterprise.*, jakarta.enterprise.*) in Java source. 2. Identify CDI scope annotations and ensure no-arg constructor pattern. 3. Convert @Inject field injection to @Inject constructor injection. 4. Preserve all JAX-RS annotations exactly. 5. For Panache entities, use open class with open mutable properties. 6. Add default values to @ConfigProperty parameters." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_418d8372 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting @ConfigProperty field injection from Java" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use @ConfigProperty on constructor parameters with a default value: @ConfigProperty(name = \"app.greeting\") val greeting: String = \"\"" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The default value satisfies CDI's no-arg constructor requirement while still allowing Quarkus to inject the configured value via the @Inject constructor." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_80e0e463 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting service return types and method signatures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Nullable return types should be used where the Java service may return null. Convert e.g. ProductDto to ProductDto? in Kotlin." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin's null safety system should reflect the actual nullability of the Java API to prevent runtime NullPointerExceptions." .

oc:kn_813b465b a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "REST resource with CDI injection — canonical conversion pattern" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "kotlin" ;
    oc:directiveContent """@Path("/api/products")
@ApplicationScoped
@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
class ProductResource @Inject constructor(
    private val productService: ProductService,
    private val pricingService: PricingService
) {
    constructor() : this(
        productService = ProductService(),
        pricingService = PricingService()
    )
}""" .

oc:kn_8a8fa7ea a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Panache ORM entities (extending PanacheEntity or PanacheEntityBase)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Panache entities must remain open classes with open mutable properties. Do NOT use data class for Panache entities." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Panache enhances field access at build time via bytecode transformation; data classes and final properties break this enhancement mechanism." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_cdc722df a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Quarkus REST resources and CDI beans" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Preserve scope annotations (@ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, @Dependent) and REST annotations (@Path, @GET, @POST, @PUT, @DELETE, @Produces, @Consumes) exactly as in Java. No annotation site target is needed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These annotations are consumed by the Quarkus/CDI runtime and must remain unchanged for the application to function correctly." .

oc:kn_d792942f a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any CDI-scoped class (@ApplicationScoped, @RequestScoped, @Dependent)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "CDI beans require a no-arg constructor (package-private or public). In Kotlin, satisfy this by giving all constructor parameters default values or by adding a secondary no-arg constructor." ;
    oc:hasRationale "CDI specification mandates a no-arg constructor for bean proxying and instantiation; Kotlin's primary constructor with parameters won't satisfy this without defaults or a secondary constructor." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_fa6715bd a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting Java classes with @Inject on fields" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Replace @Inject field injection with an @Inject-annotated primary constructor. When multiple constructors exist, CDI requires @Inject on the constructor it should use. With a single constructor, Quarkus discovers it automatically." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Kotlin idiomatic DI uses constructor injection; field injection is not idiomatic and @Inject on the primary constructor makes the dependency explicit and testable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

